🔍 C++ Static Code Analyzer
🚀 Description:
This repository contains a static code analyzer designed to detect security vulnerabilities in C++ code. The analyzer integrates with IDEs and performs code analysis to identify common weaknesses, such as buffer overflows, memory leaks, and unsafe function usage.

📂 Project Structure
📦 cpp-code-analyzer  
 ┣ 📂 src               # Source code for the analyzer  
 ┃ ┣ 📜 analyzer.cpp  
 ┃ ┣ 📜 parser.cpp  
 ┃ ┣ 📜 utils.cpp  
 ┣ 📂 tests             # Test cases for the analyzer  
 ┣ 📜 README.md  
 ┣ 📜 .gitignore  
 ┣ 📜 Makefile          # Build script  
 ┣ 📜 setup.sh          # Installation script  

⚡ Features
✅ Static Analysis – Detects vulnerabilities in C++ code
✅ IDE Integration – Works with Visual Studio Code, CLion, etc.
✅ Custom Rules Engine – Define security rules for detection
✅ Performance Optimization – Efficient scanning of large codebases
✅ Cross-Platform – Supports Windows, Linux, and macOS

🔧 Installation & Usage
1️⃣ Install Dependencies
Ensure you have GCC/Clang installed:
sudo apt update && sudo apt install g++ clang

2️⃣ Clone the Repository
git clone https://github.com/your-username/cpp-code-analyzer.git
cd cpp-code-analyzer

3️⃣ Build the Project
make

4️⃣ Run the Analyzer
Analyze a sample C++ file:
./analyzer test.cpp


